IntelSatSolver -- MaxSAT Evaluation Incremental-Track (IPAMIR) submission
=========================================================================

This directory is a self-contained incremental-track solver package. Its
signature, as returned by ipamir_signature(), is "IntelSatSolver".

Layout
------
  makefile        Default goal builds  libipamirIntelSatSolver.a  (the IPAMIR
                  static library required by the evaluation).
  glue.cc         Provides MainWallTimePassed(), normally supplied by the
                  command-line front-end (Main.cc). Main.cc's object is dropped
                  from the archive because it carries main(), which would clash
                  with the benchmark application's main().
  LIBS            Extra linker flags needed by the solver (-lpthread).
  solver_src/     Full IntelSAT (Topor) source tree, including the IPAMIR
                  interface ToporIpamir.cc and the MaxSAT algorithms
                  (algorithms/: NuWLS, Mrs. Beaver, LSU).

How it builds
-------------
  make
    1. builds the solver's release static library from solver_src (make libr),
    2. copies it to libipamirIntelSatSolver.a,
    3. removes Main.or (drops the main() symbol),
    4. adds glue.o (MainWallTimePassed),
    5. ranlib.

Usage in the IPAMIR harness
---------------------------
  Place this directory as  <ipamir>/maxsat/IntelSatSolver/  and build any
  benchmark application with:
      make IPAMIRSOLVER=IntelSatSolver
  The IPAMIR header is assumed available as ../../ipamir.h, per the maxsat/
  directory convention.

Requirements
------------
  - g++ with C++20 support (the solver uses std::span etc.).
  - POSIX threads (-lpthread).

Return codes (ipamir_solve), per the IPAMIR contract
----------------------------------------------------
  0  interrupted, no feasible solution (only via ipamir_set_terminate)
  10 interrupted, feasible solution found (only via ipamir_set_terminate)
  20 unsatisfiable hard clauses
  30 optimal solution found and proven (via the LSU complete phase)
  40 ERROR state (unsupported call sequence / internal solver error)
